<<.from-version "5.1.18">> The `\import` [[pragma|Pragmas]] is used to import macro, procedure, function, widget and variable definitions from other tiddlers that are identified by a [[Filter Expression]].

It is a shortcut syntax for the ImportVariablesWidget.

```
\import <filter>
```

<<.note "Imports can be cascaded, i.e. the imported tiddlers can themselves contain an `\import` pragma or an <<.wid importvariables>> widget.">>

!! Redefining Imported Definitions

You can use the `\define`, `\procedure`, `\function` or `\widget` pragmas, the SetWidget or the LetWidget to redefine any imported definitions after they have been imported.

! Example

!! Global Macro Definitions

The main page template [[$:/core/ui/PageTemplate]] uses the `\import` pragma to import all definitions that should be available globally via a <<.olink subfilter>> operator and a configuration tiddler: 

```
\import [subfilter{$:/core/config/GlobalImportFilter}]
```
The core config tiddler [[$:/core/config/GlobalImportFilter]] defines this filter:

<$codeblock code={{$:/core/config/GlobalImportFilter}} />

<<.note "Tiddlers are imported in the order of the <<.attr filter>> output, with subsequently imported definitions possibly overwriting preceding ones if they use the same name.
">>